records.addlTxt:
Defendant Thomas L Williams in court with attorney Danielle L. Shelton.  Kelly O'Neill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 3 MONTHS  in the House of Correction with credit for 4 days time served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR.
Conditions: 
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Perform 25 hours of community service;
*  Maintain full time employment/school;
*  Complete a course in anger management;
*  Court will waive all costs and surcharges that can be waived;  Court ordered all mandatory costs and surcharges to be paid during the term of probation.

Court will allow the termination of probation after 6 months if all terms are met.  Court will grant expungement upon successful completion of probation.
